<HelpLayout title="Sensor Types" category="Sensors & Hardware" description="Compare Plantgotchi's four sensor models and find the right one for your setup.">
  <p>
    Plantgotchi offers four sensor models, each designed for different setups. All sensors
    measure the same core metrics: soil moisture, temperature, light, and battery level.
  </p>

  <h2>BLE Child Sensor — $9–$12</h2>
  <p>
    <em>The tiny one.</em> A Bluetooth-only sensor powered by a CR2032 coin cell battery.
    It lasts up to 2 years and is perfect for pairing with a hub or parent sensor.
    Since it's BLE-only, it needs a nearby phone, Solo sensor (parent mode), or PlantCam Pro
    to relay its data.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>BLE only — no WiFi</li>
    <li>CR2032 battery, ~2-year life</li>
    <li>Smallest and cheapest option</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Solo Sensor — $15–$19</h2>
  <p>
    <em>The independent one.</em> Has both WiFi and BLE, so it can upload data directly to
    the cloud without needing a phone nearby. USB-C rechargeable with an optional OLED screen
    that shows current readings.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>WiFi + BLE connectivity</li>
    <li>USB-C rechargeable</li>
    <li>Optional OLED display</li>
    <li>Can act as a parent for BLE Child sensors</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>PlantCam — $25–$29</h2>
  <p>
    <em>The photographer.</em> Adds a 5MP camera for automatic time-lapse photos of your plant's
    growth. Takes a photo every few hours and stores it locally. Battery lasts 4–6 months.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>5MP camera with auto time-lapse</li>
    <li>4–6 month battery life</li>
    <li>All standard sensor readings included</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>PlantCam Pro — $69–$79</h2>
  <p>
    <em>The brain.</em> Built on a Raspberry Pi, this is the hub for serious plant collectors.
    It runs AI plant disease detection on-device, acts as a central hub for all your BLE Child
    sensors, and connects everything to the cloud.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>AI plant disease detection</li>
    <li>Hub for unlimited BLE Child sensors</li>
    <li>Raspberry Pi powered</li>
    <li>Always-on (USB-C powered)</li>
  </ul>

